        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 11:46AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 1146 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 6 miles
southwest of Octavia, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Octavia...                        Hodgen...
Muse...                           Honobia...
Big Cedar...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until noon CDT for southeastern
Oklahoma.</instruction>
